# This test fails on CI but passes locally
-CancelableEventTest.BothCancelFailureAndSucceedOccurUnderContention

# Upstream flake (crbug.com/325641473): the last trace event is occasionally
# missing after EndTraceAndFlush(), so the ASSERT_TRUE(dict) lookup for the
# final event fails. Chromium already disables this test on Mac for the same
# "missing last event" root cause; we observed the same failure on Linux x64
# (brave/brave-browser#55948). The race is platform-general but upstream LUCI
# Analysis reports it as stable (<1% / 60d), so this is a low-frequency flush
# race, not a Brave-specific issue — Brave only adds unrelated trace categories
# in chromium_src/base/trace_event/builtin_categories.h.
-TraceEventTestFixture.PrimitiveArgs
